<div id="heroboxAd">
    <div id="contentContainer">
    <div style="float:left; margin:5px 0 10px 0; width:650px; font-size:16pt">Need Help?</div>
    <div style="float:left; margin:0 0 25px 0; width:640px; font-size:12pt">Pivotcard is super simple to use. Just follow the steps below to get going. If you're having any trouble with the site or our services, drop us an <a href="mailto:support@pivotcard.com">email</a> and we'll get back to you asap.</div>
    <div class="supportBullet">
	<div class="blueNumber"><div style="width:100%;float:left;margin-top:1px">1</div></div>
	<div class="supportText">Create a Pivotcard name. Think of your Pivotcard name like a vanity plate for your car. It's a 
	unique one-word identifier that you want others to recognize. For example, if your name is 
	Jane Doe, you might use "janedoe" as your Pivotcard name. Or maybe you love soccer and 
	want to create your identity around the sport. You could use "soccerlvr" as your Pivotcard name.
	Your Pivotcard name is different than your user account name. 
	<br/><br/>
	<b>pivotcard.com/janedoe</b>
	<br/>
	<b>pivotcard.com/soccerlvr</b>
	</div>
</div>

    <div class="supportBullet">
	    <div class="blueNumber"><div style="width:100%;float:left;margin-top:1px">2</div></div>
	    <div class="supportText">Create Pivots. Pivots are pointers to web pages that you want to send people to (such as your
	    Facebook, Twitter or LinkedIn pages). Each Pivot needs a name, but they work best if they are
	    kept short. Abbreviations or even symbols work great because they are easy to remember and
	    quick to write down.
	    <br/><br/>
		    pivotcard.com/johndoe/<b>fb</b> - points to <b>facebook.com/john.doe</b>
	    <br/>
		    pivotcard.com/johndoe/<b>li</b> - points to <b>linkedin.com/johnqdoe</b>
	    <br/>
		    pivotcard.com/johndoe/<b>#</b> - points to <b>johnsblog.com</b>
	    </div>
    </div>

    <div class="supportBullet">
	    <div class="blueNumber"><div style="width:100%;float:left;margin-top:1px">3</div></div>
	    <div class="supportText">Create a "Pivotpage" on Pivotcard. A Pivotpage is a basic page we host for you so you don't
	    have to send your contact to another site. Create these when you need a custom identity
	    for a particular situation or create a Pivot that lists all your websites in one place.
	    </div>
    </div>
    <div class="supportBullet">
    <div class="supportText">That's it. Create as many Pivots as you'd like for social interactions, business contacts, or meeting 
    people. Be creative, go crazy, and have fun!</div>
    </div>

    </div>
